race.comment: STARSHIP IMPULSIVE (9) was prominent on the corner and battled on well to finish second last start over 1673m in Listed grade at this track (Synthetic), beaten half a length as favourite. In a suitable race and can play a major role. RAMSEY POND (4) held on well to finish second when first-up from a break last time out over 1609m at Kentucky (Turf) after leading for much of the way. Solid run last time and will take catching again. MISCHIEF IN MOTION (7) has been kept fresh since an all-the-way win over 1811m in Listed grade at Delaware Park (Turf). Has to carry more weight this time but has solid claims. CRAFTY COLLECTOR (6) had been in sound form but last start she was safely held when sixth over 1673m in stakes class at this track (Synthetic). Edwin Gonzalez has a good strike rate aboard this three-year-old filly so she is among the better chances.
